<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
      xmlns:doc="http://www.rabbitmq.com/namespaces/ad-hoc/doc"
      xmlns:r="http://www.rabbitmq.com/namespaces/ad-hoc/conformance"
      xmlns:x="http://www.rabbitmq.com/2011/extensions"
      xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2003/XInclude">
  <head>
    <title>Installing on Mac</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <doc:section name="standalone-mac">
      <h3>Download the Server</h3>
      <r:downloads signature="yes">
        <r:download absolute="yes" url="https://dl.bintray.com/rabbitmq/all/rabbitmq-server/&version-server;/rabbitmq-server-mac-standalone-&version-server;.tar.xz"
                    downloadfile="rabbitmq-server-mac-standalone-&version-server;.tar.xz">
	  Packaged for Mac systems (tar.xz) shipping Erlang &standalone-otp-version; (from <a href="https://bintray.com/rabbitmq/all">Bintray</a>)
        </r:download>
        <r:download absolute="yes" url="https://github.com/rabbitmq/rabbitmq-server/releases/download/&version-server-tag;/rabbitmq-server-mac-standalone-&version-server;.tar.xz"
                    downloadfile="rabbitmq-server-mac-standalone-&version-server;.tar.xz">
	   Packaged for Mac systems (tar.xz) shipping Erlang &standalone-otp-version; (from <a href="https://github.com/rabbitmq/rabbitmq-server/releases">GitHub</a>)
        </r:download>
      </r:downloads>

      <doc:heading>Standalone Mac</doc:heading>

      <doc:subsection name="dependencies">
        <doc:heading>Dependencies</doc:heading>
        <p>
          This package requires OpenSSL 1.0.x installed. We strongly recommend
          doing this via <a href="http://brew.sh/">Homebrew</a> to avoid possible
          issues with dynamic library paths.
        </p>
      </doc:subsection>

      <doc:subsection name="install-standalone">
        <doc:heading>Install the Server</doc:heading>
        <p>
          This build of RabbitMQ includes an Erlang runtime. That means you
          don't need to install Erlang to run RabbitMQ. The build is known to work
          with <strong>OS X</strong> versions <strong>10.6.4</strong> and above.
          If you are curious about how this works you can read more
          <a href="http://www.erlang.org/doc/design_principles/release_structure.html">here</a>.
        </p>
        <p>
          Download
          <code>rabbitmq-server-mac-standalone-&version-server;.tar.xz</code>
          from the link above.
        </p>
        <xi:include href="download-tarball.xml.inc"/>
      </doc:subsection>

      <doc:subsection name="install-homebrew">
        <doc:heading>Installation with Homebrew</doc:heading>
        <p>
          Possibly the easiest way to use this package is via <a href="http://brew.sh/">Homebrew</a>. It
          will automatically install the OpenSSL formula mentioned above:

<pre class="sourcecode bash">
brew install rabbitmq
</pre>
        </p>
      </doc:subsection>

      <xi:include href="running-generic-unix.xml.inc"/>
      <xi:include href="generic-unix-file-locations.xml.inc"/>

    </doc:section>

    <xi:include href="install-guest-localhost.xml.inc"/>
    <xi:include href="managing-the-broker.xml.inc"/>
    <xi:include href="max-open-files-limit-osx.xml.inc" />
  </body>
</html>
